Flair - combat resource
------------------------------------------------------------
Flair is a Swashbuckler's combat momentum: style, nerve,
timing, and the room's attention turning toward the blade.

Flair starts at zero and cannot be stored between logins. It
builds while fighting and decays while out of combat. Maximum
Flair is 10 plus one tenth of the Swashbuckler's charisma.

During each combat round, a Swashbuckler has a chance to
gain one Flair. Wielding a weapon personalized with
nameweapon gives an additional chance. Flourish improves
both opportunities.

A critical hit grants one Flair, at most once per combat
round.

Flair is spent by certain guild skills, including slip and
press.

see also: slip, press, flourish, nameweapon, challenge
